<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🧊 M003 Extension 2 — English Worksheet (Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Pixel-Art Mob Heads (x, y) · <strong>Course:</strong> 3D Coordinates · <strong>Level:</strong> Extension (Beginner, after Week 3) · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<p>Another <strong>bonus picture challenge</strong>. You copy a mob head onto your wall using <strong>(x, y)</strong>. x is how far <strong>across</strong>, y is how far <strong>up</strong>. Read the picture and place each block at its (x, y).</p>
<p><strong>First, build your canvas.</strong> Run this to make a blank <strong>15 × 15</strong> wall, then put a <strong>red block at your feet</strong> as your <strong>home spot</strong>:</p>
<div style="display:flex; gap:14px; align-items:flex-start; margin:10px 0; page-break-inside:avoid; break-inside:avoid"><div style="flex:1; min-width:0"><p style="margin:0 0 4px; font-weight:700">🧩 Blocks</p><img src="../assets/week3-canvas-blocks.png" alt="MakeCode blocks: on chat command run, fill with white concrete from ~1 ~1 ~0 to ~15 ~15 ~0, replace" style="width:100%; max-width:240px; border-radius:8px; display:block"></div><div style="flex:1; min-width:0"><p style="margin:0 0 4px; font-weight:700">🐍 Python</p><pre style="margin:0; white-space:pre; font-size:12px">def on_run():
    blocks.fill(WHITE_CONCRETE,
        pos(1, 1, 0),
        pos(15, 15, 0),
        FillOperation.REPLACE)
player.on_chat("run", on_run)</pre></div></div>

<blockquote>
<p>🔴 <strong>Stand on the red block every time you run.</strong> If you move, the picture moves too and the blocks land in the wrong place. Same spot every time = a clean picture.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read the steps. Before you imagine it happening, circle or write your answer.</p>
<pre><code>place green block at (4, 11)
place green block at (5, 11)
place green block at (6, 11)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Do these blocks make a line going across? Circle one:</strong> across · up</p>
<p><strong>Which number stays the same — x or y?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>place black block at (6, 6)
place black block at (6, 7)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>These share x = 6 and y grows. Do they go across or up? Circle one:</strong> across · up</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Find the Difference 🐛</h2>
<p>Each pair shows the <strong>correct</strong> line first, then a <strong>broken</strong> one. Circle what's different and write one short sentence about the bug.</p>
<p><strong>Pair A</strong> — The creeper's two eyes should be at <strong>different</strong> spots: (4, 11) and (10, 11).</p>
<pre><code># correct
place black block at (4, 11)
place black block at (10, 11)
</code></pre>
<pre><code># broken
place black block at (4, 11)
place black block at (4, 11)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? Where do both blocks land?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Pair B</strong> — The piglin's eye should be at (5, 10).</p>
<pre><code># correct
place dark block at (5, 10)
</code></pre>
<pre><code># broken
place dark block at (10, 5)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? Which two numbers got swapped?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Fill the Gap ✏️</h2>
<p>To move <strong>up</strong> a column, the <strong>second</strong> number (y) has to grow. Fill in the missing numbers so this line goes up at x = 6.</p>
<pre><code>place black block at (6, 6)
place black block at (6, __)
place black block at (6, __)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Word bank for the blanks:</strong> <code>7</code> · <code>8</code></p>
<p><strong>Write the two missing numbers:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Tell Me What You Built 📸</h2>
<p>Stand on your <strong>home spot</strong> (the red block).</p>
<p><strong>Warm up first.</strong> Copy this mini creeper face onto your wall. Read each square's (x, y) and place that color there.</p>
